developerResponse:
{'id': 30170034, 'body': "Hi Daniel, thanks so much for reaching out to us about this. When you purchase lifetime membership you have full access to Balance premium, for the lifetime of the product, without the requirement of additional purchases.

Unfortunately, it looks as though the original subscription wasn't canceled before the renewal date, which is where the second charge from Apple occurred. We apologize for any miscommunication that occurred there. We are actively reviewing our processes to ensure it's clear that members need to turn off auto-renewal on pre-existing subscriptions, once they make a lifetime purchase. While we would love to be able to help, by canceling on a member's behalf, Apple doesn't allows developers the access to Apple IDs that would be necessary to do so.

Apple is now showing that you have been refunded for the second purchase, and auto-renewal on that original subscription is turned off. As such there will be no future charges to your account. We appreciate your support and we hope you continue to enjoy using Balance. If we can help with anything else now, or in the future, don't hesitate to get in touch with us at support@balanceapp.com. ", 'modified': '2022-06-05T13:28:30Z'}
